## Chapter 17 Learn

* Watch together, learn together. Learn from each others perspective, (software engineer, marketer, designer, product manager). Each team member brings their own experience and talents to the team, try to understand from their perspective.
* Record notes as a group and collate them on a group board. Each individual note taker should label their notes with initials.
* Look for patterns, after the interview try to collate all notes under topics/events.
* Back to the future, questions were asked at the beginning of the sprint. Each watcher should try to give an quick answer to the questions that were asked at the beginning of the sprint.
* A winner every time, its a success whether the prototype works or if you haven't identified where you went wrong.
* Made for people, take the time in the interview to get better insights into the customer and the problem you're trying to solve for them.
